[SN]TITLE[SN]
Loch Ness lifeboat assists in rescue of injured biker

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Lifeboat and coastguard volunteers have been involved in the rescue of a biker who crashed and landed in a gorge near Loch Ness.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
RNLI Loch Ness was alerted to the incident near Invermoriston just before 18:30 on Thursday.
Police, ambulance and fire service personnel were also called to the scene.
The casualty, who was seriously injured, was lifted from the gorge on a stretcher and airlifted to hospital.
The biker's condition in Raigmore Hospital in Inverness was not known.
